        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.6/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>URL Shortener micro service for FreeCodeCamp</h1>
            <hr>
            
            <h3>Example Usage</h3>
            <code>
               https://calm-retreat-40288.herokuapp.com/api/shorten/new/http://www.google.com 
            </code>
            <br>
            
            <h3>Example output</h3>
            <code>
               { "original_url": "http://www.google.com", "short_url": "https://calm-retreat-40288.herokuapp.com/api/shorten/4" }
            </code>
            
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <code>
                https://calm-retreat-40288.herokuapp.com/api/shorten/4
            </code>
            <p></p>
            <p>if it's a valid id server will redirect you to website that belongs to the id.</p>
            <p>otherwise server will response with error message says "nothing found!."</p>
        </div>
